    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix CS Service Notification encoding for F1AP interface compatibility\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_cs_service_notification` function was not properly encoding the EMM message header fields (protocol discriminator, security header type, and message type) that are part of the CS Service Notification message structure. This caused F1AP interface handling errors between CU and DU, leading to message loss or corruption downstream.\n\nThis fix ensures that the complete CS Service Notification message, including the header fields, is properly encoded for transmission over the F1AP interface.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/CsServiceNotification.c`: Added encoding of protocol discriminator, security header type, and message type fields\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/EMM/MSG/CsServiceNotification.h`: Updated minimum and maximum length calculations to include header bytes\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Trigger a CS Service Notification message generation in the network\n2. Observe that the message sent over F1AP interface between CU and DU is missing the header bytes\n3. The receiving end will either reject the message or misinterpret its contents due to the missing header information\n4. This results in message loss or incorrect processing downstream\n\nThe fix ensures that the complete 4-byte minimum message (2 bytes header + 2 bytes paging identity) is properly encoded and transmitted over the F1AP interface.\n"
}